== About Me
Hello and welcome to my page!
I'm coming from [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Athens Athens, Greece],
and I'm currently a quantitative researcher at [https://voleon.com/ The Voleon Group],
where I conduct machine learning research in order to forecast the stock markets.
Before that I obtained a PhD in [https://eecs.berkeley.edu/ EECS] with a designated emphasis in [https://www2.eecs.berkeley.edu/CCS/ Statistics]
from the [https://www.berkeley.edu/ UC Berkeley], \n
where I was advised by [https://people.eecs.berkeley.edu/~satishr/?_ga=2.231748127.1296613845.1562022622-380884467.1553660237 Satish Rao].
I hold a MSc in [https://eecs.berkeley.edu/ EECS] from the [https://www.berkeley.edu/ UC Berkeley],
as well as a Diploma in [https://www.ece.ntua.gr/en ECE] from the [https://www.ntua.gr/en/ National Technical Univesity of Athens]
where \n
I was advised by [https://www.softlab.ntua.gr/~nickie/ Nikolaos Papaspyrou].

== Research
My research interests lie in the following areas:
- probability
- statistics
- information theory
- statistical learning theory
- machine learning
- stochastic control
- optimization


In particular, I have researched:
- concentration inequalities
- Markov processes
- multi-armed bandit problems
- optimal transport
